text: Halecomorphi is a type of ray-finned fish in the Neopterygii. The only living Halecomorph species are the bowfin (Amia calva) and eyespot bowfin (Amia ocellicauda).J.S. Nelson; T.C. Grande; M.V H. Wilson 2016. Fishes of the World 5th ed. Wiley. p. 752. . == Members == Here are the members of the Halecomorphi: * Ionoscopus * Amia calva * Amia ocellicauda * Parasemionotiformes * Liodesmus * Sinamia == References == Category:Ray-finned fish Category:Freshwater fish
